  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Chop the ginger and transfer to a blender with the grated coconut, chilli, daria dal (if using) and a splash of water. Blend all the ingredients, season with salt and pour into a serving bowl. You can add more or less water, depending on how thick you like your chutney."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "For the tarka, place a small saucepan over a medium heat with the oil. Once hot, add the mustard seeds, urid dal, asafoetida, curry leaves and dried red chilli. Fry for a few seconds, then pour straight over the chutney just before serving."
    }
